Plot our predicted VCF and the original VCF

Summary

Looking at the scatterplot between the original and predicted VCF, we can see that the prediction overall is quite correct. The cloud looks to be on a angle of 45 degrees. Therefore there is a relatively high correlation. Low values of the original VCF are harder to predict, and higher values are easier to get right. There are only a few locations with a VCF of lower than 5%

All the RMSE values

RMSE
cropland 7.020627
forest 3.966206
wetland 9.273279
overall 8.356770

In this table, we see that the overall RMSE is higher than the RMSE of cropland and forest. Only the RMSE of wetland higher. We also see that the RMSE of forest is roughly half the size of the overall RMSE, which is good thing because VCF is a indicator for forest.
